  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. In the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act, which require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions and conduct customer due diligence. Internationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering. These laws typically require financial institutions to implement compliance programs, report large cash transactions, and screen for potential criminal activity.",
